Package jetbrains.mps.project

Class LanguageImportHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • jetbrains.mps.project.LanguageImportHelper
  • public final class LanguageImportHelper
extends Object
    Facility to interoperate with user to add a new used language to a model/devkit. Responsible to collect user input and to access model/module internals to update respectively.

    Since this class shows UI, it takes over responsibility to control model access and executing appropriate commands.

    Configure the helper first (setOnCloseActivity(Runnable), setShortcut(ShortcutSet), then perform actual selection and modification with addUsedLanguage(SModel) or addExportedLanguage(DevKit)

    Since:
    3.4

      • setOnCloseActivity

        public LanguageImportHelper setOnCloseActivity​(@Nullable
                                               Runnable runnable)
        This is the way it used to be. Its use suggests ChooseByNamePopupComponent.invoke() returns immediately, and we need a mechanism to perform an action only once dialog to pick a language closes.

        NOTE, this is configuration method and shall be invoked prior to addExportedLanguage(DevKit) or addUsedLanguage(SModel) calls

        Parameters:
        runnable - code to execute once language to import has been picked or selection dialog has been closed
        Returns:
        this for convenience
